<p>Oh, come on, remembering this isn&#8217;t all that difficult. It&#8217;s not like it&#8217;s algebra or physics or anything along those lines. All you have to do is put it in your head once and you can remember it for a lifetime. It&#8217;s a simple as remembering that winter, spring, summer, and fall are only capitalized when they happen to be part of a proper name.</p>
